   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3176_1.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <address rend="letterhead">
                  <addrLine>The Little Orchard,</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Shoreham,</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Kent.</addrLine>
               </address>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1914-02-12">Feb 12 - 14</date>
               </dateline>

               <salute>My dear friend:</salute>
               <milestone xml:id="m01" unit="section"/>
               <milestone xml:id="m02" unit="section"/>
            </opener>

            <p>It is very nice of <add place="superimposed">you</add> to write to me so soon after
                        <choice><abbr>y<hi rend="superscript"
                  >r</hi>.</abbr><expan>your</expan></choice> marriage. Of course I <hi
                  rend="underline">was</hi> very surprised – ! But you know how much I appreciate
                  <persName ref="#ps:FlorenceHardy">her</persName>. I think she has a beautiful
               nature; <hi rend="underline">very</hi> full of sympathy, &amp; she combines, (which
               is perhaps rare –,) the qualit<subst><del>ies</del><add place="superimposed"
                  >y</add></subst> of enthusiasm, <hi rend="underline"
                           ><subst><del><unclear>a</unclear></del><add place="superimposed"
                     >wi</add></subst>th</hi> common – sense –. It will be a great <pb n="2"
                  facs="uoedh_hl_h.3176_2.jpg"/> happiness too, to you to know that she understands
               &amp; <hi rend="underline">loves</hi> your work – &amp; is so really <hi
                  rend="underline">proud</hi> of it.</p>

            <p>Thank you very much for saying you <choice><abbr>w<hi rend="superscript"
                     >d</hi>.</abbr><expan>would</expan></choice> have written earlier, had you
               thought the news <choice><abbr>w<hi rend="superscript"
                     >d</hi>.</abbr><expan>would</expan></choice> reach <placeName ref="#pl:London"
                  >London</placeName> so soon. I saw the pictures in different <pb n="3"
                  facs="uoedh_hl_h.3176_3.jpg"/> papers with great interest. If you come to
                  <placeName ref="#pl:London">London</placeName> in warmer days, you must both spend
                  <hi rend="underline">a long day</hi> with me here? The station is only a mile off,
               &amp; the journey an hour from <placeName ref="#pl:VictoriaStation"
                  >Victoria</placeName>.</p>

            <p>This belated enclosure from <persName ref="#ps:StewartEllis">Mr Ellis</persName>
               <choice><abbr>sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>.</abbr><expan>should</expan></choice>
               have gone to you long before. Needless to say, <hi rend="underline">I</hi> did not
               write to the Press. Many people <pb n="4" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3176_4.jpg"/> might have
               thought it an impertinence on my part.–</p>

            <p>I <choice><abbr>sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>.</abbr><expan>should</expan></choice>
               <hi rend="underline">so</hi> like to know what our mutual friends &amp; acquaintances
               wrote about <choice><abbr>y<hi rend="superscript"
                  >r</hi>.</abbr><expan>your</expan></choice> marriage? <persName
                  ref="#ps:EdmundGosse">Mr Gosse</persName>, <persName ref="#ps:ClementShorter">Mr
                  Shorter</persName> – <persName ref="#ps:FrederickWedmore">Sir F.
                  Wedmore</persName> – <persName ref="#ps:BirdieIlchester">Birdie
                  Ilchester</persName> &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c! Some day you will tell me–?–</p>

            <p>I have let my <placeName ref="#pl:HydeParkSquare">London house</placeName> for a
               time, &amp; hope to let it again. Do tell your wife to write to</p>

            <pb n="5" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3176_5.jpg"/>
            <ab>
               <seg xml:id="h3176a" corresp="#m01" style="transform:rotateZ(-90deg)">me very soon.
                  It <choice><abbr>w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>.</abbr>
                     <expan>would</expan></choice> be a real pleasure &amp; interest to hear all
                           <choice><abbr>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></abbr>
                     <expan>your</expan></choice> news.</seg>
            </ab>

            <closer xml:id="h3176b" corresp="#m02" style="transform:rotateZ(-90deg)">
               <salute><choice><abbr>Ev</abbr><expan>Ever</expan></choice>
                  <choice><abbr>yr</abbr><expan>your</expan></choice>
                  <choice><abbr>affec.</abbr><expan>affectionate</expan></choice> friend.</salute>
               <signed>FH</signed>
            </closer>



